sentences: Kevin Norton (born January 21, 1956) is an American percussionist and composer active in the New York City jazz and contemporary music scenes.
In 1999, he founded Barking Hoop Recordings, a record label dedicated to releasing new and original music.
Kevin Norton has also spent summers at camp Encore/Coda in Maine teaching music theory classes and private percussion classes.
Norton would later record the album The Judge's Decision with Hinton in 1986.
Beginning in 1998, Norton is currently teaching at William Paterson University.
Beginning in 1998, Norton is currently teaching at William Paterson University.
He began the Barking Hoop label in 1999 with a live concert recording of a piece he composed for the French situationist theorist Guy Debord, "with Braxton cast as sideman.
recently, Norton has been working in various configurations with musicians Tony Malaby, Dave Ballou, John Lindberg, Scott Robinson, Connie Crothers, and J. D. Parran.
